==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Skirling
<hw>Skirl"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A shrill cry or sound; a crying
shrilly; a skirl.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng. & Scot.]</mark> <rj><au>Sir W.
Scott.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>When the <qex>skirling</qex> of the pipes cleft the air his cold
eyes softened.</q> <rj><qau>Mrs. J. H. Ewing.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Skirling</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Skirling
<hw>Skirl"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A small trout
or salmon; -- a name used loosely.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Skirmish</ent>⟦br⟧
